ACT ΙΙ. SCENE 3.

The manuscripts indicate here the beginning of a new scene. There is no change in the characters upon the stage, but Philocrates has, during most of the preceding interview, been standing apart. Hegio now crosses over to talk with him, and this makes the forming of a new soene not unnatural.
